established to manage the first steps of privatization because of hungarys  billion foreign debt the government decided to sell state property instead of distributing it to the people for free the spa was attacked by populist groups because several companies management had the right to find buyers and discuss sale terms with them thus stealing the company another reason for discontent was that the state offered large tax subsidies and environmental investments which sometimes cost more than the selling price of the company along with the acquisition of companies foreign investors launched many greenfield investments the centerright hungarian democratic forum government of – decided to demolish agricultural cooperatives by splitting them up and giving machinery and land to their former members the government also introduced a recompensation law which offered vouchers to people who had owned land before it was nationalized in  these people or their descendants could exchange their vouchers for land previously owned by agricultural cooperatives who were forced to give up some of their land for this purpose small stores and retail businesses were privatized between  and  however greenfield investments by foreign retail companies like tesco cora and ikea had a much bigger economic impact many public utilities including the national telecommunications company matáv the national oil and gas conglomerate mol group and electricity supply and production companies were privatized as well though most banks were sold to foreign investors the largest bank national savings bank otp remained hungarianowned  of the shares were sold to foreign institutional investors and given to the social security organizations  were bought by employees and  was offered at the budapest stock exchange hungarys economy since edit gdp growth inflation and active population in hungary  gdp per capita in usd at  market prices in hungary  general government gross debt in hungary amongst other countries a